        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/5/67",
        "text": [
          " أَبُو جَعْفَرٍ اَلْبَاقِرُ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ: «إِذَا دَخَلَ اَلْوَقْتُ وَجَبَ اَلطَّهُورُ وَ اَلصَّلاَةُ وَ لاَ صَلاَةَ إِلاَّ بِطَهُورٍ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.67 - Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as) said:\n\"When the time for prayer enters, purification (ablution) and the prayer become obligatory, and there is no prayer without purification.\""
          ]
        }
